<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101216422331268></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101216422331268><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=91720&mid=101216422331268>Tales</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=91720&mid=101216422331268#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=91720><span id= >roshi the Charming</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>103 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Jan 27th 4:45 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.51]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>This week I begin “Tales From Anarchy Online”, a biweekly look at one of the most underrated MMORPGs around.<br><br>In AO, I play Lichoon, a level 40 Martial Artist (closest thing to an EQ monk) and Redtaped a Level 21 Bureaucrat (Similar to an EQ Enchanter, except our pets are allot cooler.) The story that follows is similar in style to my satire of role-playing I wrote a while ago. While it may seem hypocritical of me to write this way, the purposes of that rant and this rant are different. In this rant I am teaching trough story telling and my character will only do stuff that you can do in the game (1.e not having huge conversations with NPCs, as seem in other stories). This story is through the eyes of Redtaped. Note: a various points I will interrupt the story in italic to clarify point.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;    <br> Tale 1: a dreary day.<br><br>As I wind my way through the clean and eerily empty street of Omni-entertainment in my beat up old mig(the game features drivable boats, cars and planes. The mig is a car.), I heard the whines and chirps of Civil Servant, my trusty robot slave (you can name your pets in this game) trying desperately to keep up behind me on my way to do Omni-Tek’s dirty work. <br><br>   I am a Bureaucrat, the master of paper pushing and our ranks are small due to the universal disdain of middle managers.  (crats are rare due to the fact that they were not implemented at release and are  slightly gimped) Therefore I am alone forced to meet the   threat of the clans with just my powerful yet not very intelligent servant and my gun. <br>The clans, until recently infested Omni-1, but due to Omni-Tek’s rule of no fighting in the city or near guards, I could not touch them. But now that the amnesty is lifted, the clanners have left our city and our lands and gone home. (PVP is zone based and the amnesty is part of the storyline.)<br><br> But they remain. They lurk inside long forgotten building and caves that no one dares to enter.  Therefore the invisible Omni-Tek executives have recruited their employees to go fish them out for sometimes meager rewards. And that is what I am going to do. I come the building where they told me to go and enter. Inside, I find dozens of them all scum. So I continue to clear them out, one by one until they die. When I completed my mission, I receive my reward, a baseball bat, some cash and token, which can be exchanged for powerful talisman (this is a token board, when you get a certain number of them, you get a board with certain stats). So I leave and go back to the mission terminal and start the process again and again until I get so bored, I go to sleep. <br><br>I wish for the day that I can leave the city and all its blandness and see the vast interesting world. I also hope that I maybe even will get involved in something important, but I doubt that because I know that only a select few really make the tide turn in this conflict. (Most of the story line comes of a website) However, I continue on hoping one day to see the sun rise over a completely Clan-free planet.     <br> <br>The End.<br>P.S.<br>The missions, cars and zone based combat apply to the clans and neutrals as well. I have not talked about the neutrals, but I will.<br>Roshi out. <br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
