<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=10108748738340></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f10108748738340><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=91720&mid=10108748738340>The REAL problem with DAOC</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=91720&mid=10108748738340#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=91720><span id= >roshi the Charming</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>103 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Jan 12th 5:34 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.55]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well from now on I will stay away from doing rants like the last one, NOT!!! If I actually stopped doing rants from the amount of hatred I got, I would have quit a long ago. Anyway I am going skiing next week so no time to update, so the rant is here early. <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;      DAOC seems to spin in a downward spiral. Why? Because Mythic is not balancing classes in both PVE and RVR, and not adding more PVE content. People speculate that Mythic is just being a bunch of jerks and is turning into Funcom (yea right….). I have the correct answer though. This may not be true, but I have proof. Mythic bit off more than they could chew with this game. Mythic simply does not have the resources to handle a game this big. <br>    <br>  Lets start with classes. DAOC has a grad total of 33 classes, yes THIRTY-THREE classes. That is allot of classes, 2 times as many classes as EQ, with 15 and AO, with 12. Now if they were simply cookie-cutter classes of each other, we would not have that much of a problem because one fix would effect all three realms. However, they are not the same in each realm, so many of the classes that need fixing have problems unique to themselves.<br><br> Lets take the shaman and warden as examples. The shaman and the warden are the secondary healers in Midguard and Hibernia respectively. The warden suffers from a lack of attack damage via melee. The shaman’s main attack line, cave magic, is useless. Even though they are in same boat, their problem areas are unique to their specific class.  Now that the headache with support classes and apply to all three realms and both PVE and RVR and you can see the mess. But we are not done.<br><br>Each realm is small and shallow the higher level you go. The realms are so small that can be can be crossed vertically on a horse in less than 20 minutes. There is even speculation that even if you put the 3 realms together, they are still smaller than EQ at release and maybe even AO. Also, the shallowness gets so bad at higher levels that basically you either do RVR or just kill in dungeons. The problem here is that each realm, with the exception of the frontiers are their own separate worlds. They each must have cities, dungeons and places to hunt in equal numbers. Not only that, they must also be different in appearance and design. I also believe that if Mythic adds a zone to one realm they must add a realm to all three. This is why each realm is so small. But we are still not done.<br><br>The RVR game is almost a separate entity from the PVE game. It has different rules and benefits than the PVE game. Mythic has the job of making RVR not only meaningful, but fun. Mythic, to there credit, has implemented some rewards, but they seem to be unbalanced. RVR must only be fun. No Hibernian or Albionian wants to be mowed down by Midguard or NPC guards of any realm.  Therefore Mythic must balance each realm as well as each class and make sure the NPC guards do not own the players.<br><br>	Now, add those 3 points together and it equals one big mess. If they would stop fixing monster skins and devoted a patch to class balancing, a series of content patches (If  Funcom is adding dungeons WITHOUT an expansion pack, Mythic can do it) and  a RVR patch then things would be farther along, but there not. They could fix it but there not because it seems to me that they are tackling everything at once and so not much is getting done.<br><br>I hope I have showed you Mythic’s true problem. There is nothing that  we can do  in the short tem other than waiting for the patches to come. On a side note, Mythic started on an expansion pack to Daoc as soon, or even before DAOC was released. Now to official reason was, I believe, that the game would be so popular it warranted an expansion. I think now the true reason was because Mythic knew then what we know now, that the game was so small and shallow so that they have to release an expansion to keep players interested over the long run (this is the reason for any expansion pack to an game but I think it is especially true in this case.). Mythic knew they a had a ticking time-bomb, they knew that when players found out it was not was slated to be, they would become angry; however it was a time-bomb that went of way too soon. Lets just hope the pack arrives in time to pick up the rubble.<br><br>Roshi out.<br><br>P.S. If your wondering about AO, Funcom got there act together and 13.6 is looking to be a good patch with some real changes and TWO static dungeons.<br> <br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
