	   <tr><td colspan=2>A very special Roshi’s rants.<br><br>Today my focus my seem strange but bear with me, I am going to talk about Dave Thomas, the founder of Wendy’s. Why am I going to talk about Dave Thomas, is because he was last of a breed, A CEO and founder who put his face and image out for all to see. He did commercials served food at Wendy’s and made the company feel like it was home spun. While Dave may or may not have been CEO at the time of his death, I at least though he was and could recognize his face anywhere and think of Wendy’s. Dave was rare in today’s corporate world, someone only rivaled by Cornel Sanders of KFC or Bill Gates.<br><br>	This brings up a point, why aren’t CEOs at the forefront of companies tactics, sure Mark Daniels is there for the customers but Sanya Jacobs is really the only true contact at Mythic. But he’s really the only one. The CEO at Sony said he hated customers. The CEO of Funcom is unknown. Do you know who the CEO is of EA, Microsoft (Bill Gates stepped down), Sega and Nintendo AT&amp;T, GE and CBS, sure few might but not a whole lot. <br><br>What I am getting at is that CEOs who are known help build brand recognition. Cornel Sanders did, Bill Gates did and Dave Thomas did. When CEOs become well know companies becomes less of giant unknown entity and seem more as collection of people and build brand images. Dave Thomas I’ll miss you and I am sure many others will too. I send my deepest condolences to his family and friends.<br><br>Roshi out.<br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
