	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hey.<br><br>Sadly, I do indeed agree with a lot of what you said.&nbsp;&nbsp;(In other rants, as well as this one.)  But, I sometimes think that many people seem to forget that Sony are not alone in their practices.<br><br>Au contraire...<br>The behaviour of Sony in the way they run Everquest is very much the norm.  Every company that finds itself in a position to abuse it's customer base, invariably seems to do so<br><br><i>I refer you to another Dilbert cartoon.  The boss suggests that it is no longer acceptable to mere 'satisfy' the customer, but they must now 'delight' the customer.  However, when suggestions such as ceasing 'price gouging' are made, the boss states that what he had in mind was a vision statement.<br><br>Indeed, my university has recently announced their new vision:  &quot;Putting the student at the centre!&quot;  However, you will notice that your wallet is pretty close to your centre of gravity and I assure you that that is where their interest lies.  (Evidence:  I am halfway through my third year and I now know more about Visual Basic programming than my lecturers!  Am I getting value for money?  I don't think so.  (I'm paying about £30/hr I'm in contact with a lecturer.  (About $50/hr)  And you have to remember this is time shared with 20 - 80 students, not alone!(It's actually even worse than it looks.  I'm only paying one third of my fees.  So they're actually gouging an hourly rate of around £90/hr!  ($150/hr)</i><br><br>The thing is, you meet this every day.  It's such a normal part of your life, that you don't even see it!  My girlfriend is currently working for directory enquires.  The cost to the customer for calling is pretty close to calling a premium rate sex line!  The company have a vision that every call should be, 'a positive moment of truth'!  But at the same time they take the attitude that they want you off the line in around twenty seconds <b>and</b> that if the details you want don't appear immediately, you don't get anything!<br>(Believe me, there are few things more annoying than calling, speaking to an abrupt telephonist, then being dumped on an automated teller, that states, 'The number you require is ex-directory!'  (I seriously always expect it to laugh and say, '%&amp;#@ you, we have your money now, fool!'<br><br>Remember, you pay whether you get the number or not!  <i>&quot;By agreeing to this license you hereby agree to throw your money at said corporations without guarantee of fun and enjoyment.&quot;</i>  That's nothing.  With this one, you get to throw your money away, without even guaranteeing you'll get the damned service, let alone that you'll like it!!!<br><br>Anyhow, I gotta go, I should be working!  *Grin*  Anyone wanna build me a door entry interface?<br><br>See ya in Norrath.<br><br>AlAaraaf.<br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Dec 12 08:27:30 2001</em><br>&nbsp;<br>"Te aurdire no possum. Musa sapienum fixa est in aura."</td></tr>
