	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hello and welcome to this weeks rant, which is on DAOC:<br><br>If you read the Daoc message boards, one thing becomes clear, DOAC should not have been released unfinished due to broken classes (rouge classes) no content for high levels and an entirely broken realm (Hibernia). No I play the game, I see those problems associated with it, and they are there. However, It becomes clear that most of this bitching is ungrounded and frankly evident of hurt emotions than a broken game.<br><br>Before Daoc was released people(fanboys) said that Doac would be the end-all of MMORPGs. The RvR would be fantastic, the game is beautiful, it would be stable, eq will die. However, when the game was released it perfectly clear that the game was not perfect at all. The game is good, but unfinished. Now 2 months after release, Daoc boards are in distinguishable from eq boards. People are bitching, moaning and complaining that “doac sucks,” ”Doac will fail when ShadowBane is released” and “mythic equals the devil” People have ignored the good of the game and focused on the bad.&nbsp;&nbsp;They are even praising the “All mighty Everquest”. Why? Simple, broken promises and a realization the mythic is like everyone else.<br>People got their hopes up that this game would be the greatest, and when they realized it happens to be flawed, people get mad, really mad. When people get hurt, they get mad. However, people need to realize that mythic is a company of people, not robots and Its JUST A GAME!!!! What I say for everyone to take a chill pill and just go play, the game is getting better, and it just takes time. While there is no excuse for an unfinished game; that is the state of the MMORPG industry and will never be completely finished.  You think the next waves of MMORPGs are going to be any different? Maybe but I would not count on it. Besides if you leave now, you will never see if the game becomes awesome.<br> On a side note: I would like to apologize to the EQ players for my actions pervious to this because now I feel that I am acting like a hypocrite. However Doac has been out for 2 months, EQ for 3 years. For people to make a fair judgment, wait until Daoc has been out  a year. Besides I never really hated eq until I left and I am thinking of playing on Luclin(I am not restarting my other characters) . The main reason why I left was the unbearable downtime, but I’ve heard its getting better.<br><br>Roshi out.<br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
