<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100732114875904></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100732114875904><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=91720&mid=100732114875904>roleplay satire</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=91720&mid=100732114875904#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=91720><span id= >The One and Only roshi</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>103 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Dec 2nd 2:25 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.36]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Since 90% of my rants seem to land with a “THUD”, I am going to try something else today:<br>REAL ROLEPLAYING.<br>See I read the other journals here and the only ones who are close to catching my post numbers are 3 role-playing journals. I find them entirely cheesy and fail to address medding, camping and zone wide communication. Not that I have anything against them, but role-playing eq (or Daoc for that matter) is a little hard. So without further ado, here is my version of a role-playing tale:<br><br>Bigbottoms Rnice, a 35th season Orge warrior, was standing on the bridge from Iceclad to Eastern wastes. It was 70 degrees outside but covered with ice, how else could barbarians make runs to their “stuff”. He was lonely, he wondered all around to the usual spots people gather, but no one was there. He wanted experience so bad, so he could tell his “human wife” that he had made it out of the long seasons of his existence. So he filled his lungs with air, and shouted out,<br>“lvl 35th warrior LFG”.<br>After a long pause, he heard a voice so close it felt like only he could hear it, and it said:<br>“Moonflower says’ come to fort’”<br><br>So he left the bridge and started walking to the fort. He saw many animals and monsters that looked red, blue and black trough his “con sense” and decided to avoid them all because he knew, that even though he was a warrior, he could not tank it without some help.<br><br>Bigbottoms made it to the fort and saw: Moonflower Nightwind, a bodacious 37th high elf cleric; Lakanar Mysticinferno, a poor forgotten 39th male barbarian shaman (p.s. I am sure you can guess who that is ;), Woochan Slither,&nbsp;&nbsp;a 40th iskar male monk, Zappermoniker, a 45 darkelf enchanter and last but not least, Heywood Jablowme, a 41st paladin with stuff he has never seen before.<br> <br>Moonflower invited him in and they sat, and sat and sat.<br>“Why are we taking so long,” Bigbottoms asked.<br>“Because I have to med and Zap is afk.” <br>“I can heal” Lakanar said.<br>“ROFL” Heywood said.<br>Another 5 minutes of waiting passed and finally Zapper returned.<br>“Back, sorry had to let the mangy mutt out and kiss the lady of the house” Zapper said. <br>“I love dogs” lakanar said <br>“Cannnnn I get a sssssssow?” Whoochan asked.<br>“Sure,” Lakanar said and he sowed the group.<br><br>So whoochan ran to the fort and pulled some orcs. Whoochan puched and Heywood slashed and Bigbottoms tanked. Moonflower healed, Zapper mezzed and Lakanar did nothing except sit there and dot occasionally.  They did this for hour after hour after hour after hour; until a druid showed up.  The druid, Hiram, decided to quadkite some orcs. Now, this was right after the chief and his oracles spawned. So when Hiram ran in the chief called all the orcs after him. Faster than a speeding bullet Hiram raced out, and the whole fort can chrashing down on the poor group and all Bigbottoms heard for 5 minutes afterwards was:<br>“Loading, please wait.”<br>BigBottoms arrived at his bind point in Iceclad all alone he felt less experienced now and was  not any closer to 36, now he was several hours away. Bigbottoms, through his telepathic link to the group said:<br>“God dammit”<br>“Ill rez you all when I get back to your corpse. You’re the only one that died, the rest of us zoned in” Moonflower said over his telepathic link.<br>And so Bigbottoms waited and waited and waited some more. Then he magically teleported to his corpse and he felt no more experienced as he was before he started.<br>“Sorry Bigbottoms, you were the only one that died. the rest of us ran into the fort. Good thing i have my Jboots and Firey Defender” Heywood said.<br>“That’s ok.”<br>Then Bigbottoms noticed something. No one was moving. When he tried to move, he went nowhere He screamed out and no one heard anything He felt himself fading away. Then it all went black and the last thing he saw was: <br>“YOU HAVE BEEN DISCONNECTED.”<br><br>Does this sound familiar to you? Well it should because this happens all the time in EQ. This is actually based off a real occurrence of mine. Most of the names have been made up, except mine and I made myself a member of the group instead of telling this from my perspective.<br>Roshi out.<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
